MLMs can accommodate the hierarchical structure of CEA data from CRTs29,31 (model 1). Suppose that the costs (c) and effects (e) for the ith individual, within the jth cluster, in the kth trial arm, follow a certain distribution characterized by its mean (µijk) and standard deviation (σ). The clustering is explicitly recognized by including parameters (
u j c
,
u j e
) to account for the cluster-specific random effects. The correlation between the individual costs and effects is introduced through the parameter θ. This bivariate model can then report incremental costs (
β 1 c
) and effects (
β 1 e
) after allowing for the clustering and correlation.
